{"key":"processedPost-9499025","value":{"id":9499025,"first":9498974,"last":9504058,"when":1230347179,"utime":"12/27/08 05:06 AM","content":"Is the bottom separating?&nbsp; If so, it's probably from clogged filters, which cause the PC pressure to return to zero before the jars pressure does.&nbsp; If jars have internal pressure, they'll break, usually by the bottom part separating.<br /><br />A fix is to turn the burner the pressure cooker is on to 'low' for ten minutes or so before going to 'off'.&nbsp; This will slow down the return to zero psi.<br /><br />Some of my jars are over 20 years old.&nbsp; I break more when canning fruits than pc'ing grains due to the fruits holding more mass and thus holding pressure if I accidentally put the rings on too tight.<br />RR","title":"Re: The Sad life of a Quart Jar."}}